262
00:12:43.135 --> 00:12:44.175
a space where they learn,

263
00:12:44.365 --> 00:12:46.335
express themselves, and seek support.

264
00:12:46.645 --> 00:12:47.935
When traditional services

265
00:12:48.035 --> 00:12:49.775
or supports are out of reach,

266
00:12:50.655 --> 00:12:52.945
youthline does not support a blanket ban on social

267
00:12:52.945 --> 00:12:54.225
media for under sixteens.

268
00:12:54.935 --> 00:12:57.235
Not only are bans extremely difficult to enforce,

269
00:12:57.545 --> 00:13:00.235
they risk pushing young people towards unregulated

270
00:13:00.235 --> 00:13:01.635
and more harmful platforms.

271
00:13:02.225 --> 00:13:04.795
They could also cut off critical pathways to connection,

272
00:13:05.195 --> 00:13:09.035
identity and support, especially for those already, uh,

273
00:13:09.035 --> 00:13:12.035
experiencing existing mental health concerns, those

274
00:13:12.035 --> 00:13:14.675
that are rainbow, identifying young people in care

275
00:13:14.815 --> 00:13:17.075
and those in rural or isolated communities.

276
00:13:17.665 --> 00:13:18.955
Instead, we urge the committee

277
00:13:18.975 --> 00:13:21.115
to focus on evidence-based systemic change.

278
00:13:21.655 --> 00:13:23.115
What's needed is not exclusion,

279
00:13:23.115 --> 00:13:24.675
but education and safer design.

280
00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:27.905
We recommend the following actions are taken

281
00:13:28.575 --> 00:13:31.185
enforcing stronger regulation of digital platforms,

282
00:13:31.185 --> 00:13:33.265
including mandatory content moderation,

283
00:13:33.655 --> 00:13:34.945
algorithm transparency

284
00:13:35.165 --> 00:13:37.865
and safety by design measures a review

285
00:13:37.865 --> 00:13:39.745
of the Harmful Digital Communications Act.

286
00:13:39.745 --> 00:13:43.225
As well overdue, we need to support long-term reform

287
00:13:43.225 --> 00:13:46.225
that prioritizes platform safety and youth rights.

288
00:13:46.895 --> 00:13:47.915
We need to embed digital

289
00:13:48.015 --> 00:13:49.315
and media literacy in the

290
00:13:49.315 --> 00:13:50.915
curriculum starting in primary school.

291
00:13:51.495 --> 00:13:52.715
And young people need the tools

292
00:13:52.735 --> 00:13:55.315
to critically navigate misinformation, harmful content,

293
00:13:55.535 --> 00:13:57.035
and the influence of algorithms.

294
00:13:57.895 --> 00:13:59.075
We need to support our parents

295
00:13:59.135 --> 00:14:00.915
and caregivers, especially those

296
00:14:00.915 --> 00:14:03.875
with lower digital literacy, through accessible,

297
00:14:04.275 --> 00:14:05.675
culturally relevant resources

298
00:14:05.855 --> 00:14:07.955
and not just complex digital control tools.

299
00:14:08.975 --> 00:14:11.155
We need to include young people in decision making,

300
00:14:11.495 --> 00:14:13.875
policy development, and platform co-design.

301
00:14:14.365 --> 00:14:16.955
Their insight is not only valid, it is essential.

302
00:14:17.545 --> 00:14:18.795
Finally, we recognize

303
00:14:18.795 --> 00:14:20.835
that online harm doesn't happen in a vacuum.

304
00:14:21.735 --> 00:14:26.275
It reflects broader issues like inequality, climate anxiety,

305
00:14:26.915 --> 00:14:28.795
