00:23:40.455 --> 00:23:42.535
where in the technology stack we should

519
00:23:43.135 --> 00:23:45.520
actually put in place the regulation at the website level,

520
00:23:45.625 --> 00:23:47.925
the platform level, at the browser, at the app store,

521
00:23:47.945 --> 00:23:50.605
at the device, or at the internet infrastructure providers.

522
00:23:51.385 --> 00:23:54.645
My team's suggestion is that regulation at the device level

523
00:23:55.075 --> 00:23:56.405
with tie-ins to browsers

524
00:23:56.405 --> 00:23:58.725
and app stores is going to be the most effective

525
00:23:58.985 --> 00:24:01.285
and have the fewest trade-offs in many instances,

526
00:24:01.785 --> 00:24:04.765
in comparisons to a lot of the other forms of regulation.

527
00:24:05.505 --> 00:24:08.325
If a device is in control, purchases

528
00:24:08.345 --> 00:24:10.165
or sellers of the device can ensure

529
00:24:10.165 --> 00:24:12.885
that the device itself is set to identify

530
00:24:12.885 --> 00:24:14.165
that it belongs to a minor.

531
00:24:14.625 --> 00:24:16.925
And this helps to ensure that adults are not

532
00:24:16.925 --> 00:24:19.845
otherwise impacted by any regulatory regime.

533
00:24:19.845 --> 00:24:22.525
This does not mean that you can't regulate platforms in

534
00:24:22.525 --> 00:24:23.645
other ways, but a lot

535
00:24:23.645 --> 00:24:25.725
of the more stringent regulations are

536
00:24:25.725 --> 00:24:26.845
best applied to the devices.

537
00:24:27.515 --> 00:24:30.805
Devices also serve as the primary gatekeeper for access

538
00:24:30.945 --> 00:24:32.845
to all different contents and services.

539
00:24:33.385 --> 00:24:36.005
So if the device does not permit the installation of an app

540
00:24:36.625 --> 00:24:39.005
to certain communications or to certain platforms

541
00:24:39.385 --> 00:24:41.885
or restricts the use of circumvention technologies,

542
00:24:42.355 --> 00:24:45.405
this also provides a fairly reasonable level of assurance

543
00:24:45.465 --> 00:24:49.325
and efficacy with fewer trade-offs for privacy, security,

544
00:24:49.505 --> 00:24:51.925
the cost of regulation to small entities

545
00:24:51.985 --> 00:24:53.325
and also to civil liberties.

546
00:24:54.075 --> 00:24:56.445
This, of course, does not preclude imposing reasonable

547
00:24:56.445 --> 00:24:57.445
duties on platforms,

548
00:24:57.445 --> 00:24:58.725
and I don't want to give that impression.

549
00:24:59.465 --> 00:25:00.965
But we have to also take care

550
00:25:00.965 --> 00:25:04.125
that if we do impose regulations on platforms

551
00:25:04.125 --> 00:25:06.485
and websites that we don't inadvertently

552
00:25:06.625 --> 00:25:09.045
and unreasonably disadvantage individuals

553
00:25:09.345 --> 00:25:12.165
or smaller platforms and businesses who also host websites.

554
00:25:12.165 --> 00:25:15.045
And we've seen this in the UK recently, technologies

555
00:25:15.045 --> 00:25:17.525
that regulators worldwide as suggesting

556
00:25:17.605 --> 00:25:19.525
to mitigate harms each come

557
00:25:19.525 --> 00:25:22.565
with seriously different sociotechnical trade-offs.

558
00:25:22.985 --> 00:25:24.645
And all too often we're finding

559
00:25:24.675 --> 00:25:27.685
that the differing profile in the different technologies

560
00:25:27.995 --> 00:25:31.085
that can be used to regulate is not brought to the fore

561
00:25:31.105 --> 00:25:32.805
during the decision making processes.

562
00:25:32.805 --> 00:25:35.165
And this is something that we would urge New Zealand

563
00:25:35.185 --> 00:25:36.525
to thoroughly consider.

564
00:25:37.265 --> 00:25:39.725
I'm very happy to answer any questions from the committee,

565
00:25:40.105 --> 00:25:42.845
but especially those relating to the design of technologies

566
00:25:42.905 --> 00:25:44.885
and platforms, the risk profile

567
00:25:44.885 --> 00:25:46.965
of intervention technologies, the viability

568
00:25:46.985 --> 00:25:50.325
and efficacy of different types of interventions, as well

569
00:25:50.425 --> 00:25:53.285
as the impact of regulations that we've seen elsewhere.

570
00:25:53.695 --> 00:25:56.205
Thank you very much and I'm happy to take any questions.

571
00:25:57.865 --> 00:26:01.005
Um, thank you so much. Um, are we too late?

