00:28:51.025 --> 00:28:54.285
And that might mean actually ticking the box when you buy a

645
00:28:54.285 --> 00:28:56.045
phone that says, yes, I'm a parent.

646
00:28:56.385 --> 00:28:57.445
Yes, this is for a kid.

647
00:28:57.745 --> 00:28:59.845
So the idea is to again, deal

648
00:28:59.845 --> 00:29:01.805
with both the technological constraints,

649
00:29:01.805 --> 00:29:03.845
the policy constraints, and to deal with some

650
00:29:03.845 --> 00:29:06.765
of these ethical issues to come to a regulatory solution

651
00:29:06.765 --> 00:29:08.645
that is more than just sounds good.

652
00:29:08.705 --> 00:29:10.325
If we say, okay, it's on the platforms

653
00:29:10.325 --> 00:29:13.285
because they built this, that doesn't mean that just

654
00:29:13.285 --> 00:29:14.565
because we feel good about

655
00:29:14.815 --> 00:29:16.285
where we're putting the responsibility

656
00:29:16.285 --> 00:29:18.285
that it's gonna be the right regulatory decision.

657
00:29:18.745 --> 00:29:20.925
As much as that's quite politically palatable.

658
00:29:21.555 --> 00:29:23.445
Vanessa, Thank you.

