00:56:06.885 --> 00:56:08.965
including porn, intimate image sharing,

1281
00:56:09.185 --> 00:56:11.965
and more recently online misogyny and deep fakes.

1282
00:56:12.585 --> 00:56:15.525
So at deep fake is the creation of a sexual image

1283
00:56:15.545 --> 00:56:16.605
of a person doing

1284
00:56:16.665 --> 00:56:19.125
or saying something that they did not say or do.

1285
00:56:19.545 --> 00:56:22.485
So this can be more accurately termed AI

1286
00:56:22.485 --> 00:56:23.685
generated sexual abuse.

1287
00:56:24.505 --> 00:56:26.005
I'm interested in this inquiry

1288
00:56:26.145 --> 00:56:28.365
as my research has demonstrated that young people

1289
00:56:28.875 --> 00:56:31.925
have both positive and negative experiences online.

1290
00:56:32.585 --> 00:56:35.245
So those positive experiences center around learning,

1291
00:56:35.255 --> 00:56:37.645
connecting with others, exploring their identities,

1292
00:56:37.895 --> 00:56:40.285
expressing themselves a place to escape

1293
00:56:40.585 --> 00:56:42.125
and somewhere to maintain their

1294
00:56:42.125 --> 00:56:43.245
friendships and relationships.

1295
00:56:44.685 --> 00:56:46.965
Research participants have reported that the internet,

1296
00:56:46.965 --> 00:56:48.245
particularly social media,

1297
00:56:48.785 --> 00:56:52.165
as a space which allows them voice and a sense of agency.

1298
00:56:53.585 --> 00:56:55.125
So some negative experiences

1299
00:56:55.355 --> 00:56:58.085
that they've reported include gendered harm, such

1300
00:56:58.085 --> 00:57:00.525
as image-based sexual abuse, harassment,

1301
00:57:00.625 --> 00:57:03.285
and the increase of AI generated sexual abuse images

1302
00:57:03.745 --> 00:57:05.005
and online misogyny.

1303
00:57:05.865 --> 00:57:08.125
Now, online misogyny harms all young people

1304
00:57:08.195 --> 00:57:10.325
through adverse mental health impacts,

1305
00:57:10.475 --> 00:57:13.365
normalizing gendered inequality, limiting girls

1306
00:57:13.365 --> 00:57:16.125
and young women's participation, fueling radicalization

1307
00:57:16.185 --> 00:57:19.765
and violence, and harming relationships and peer cultures.

1308
00:57:20.505 --> 00:57:23.485
Online misogyny isn't just words, it actively shapes

1309
00:57:23.485 --> 00:57:25.925
how young people think, fail, interact,

1310
00:57:25.985 --> 00:57:27.205
and imagine their futures.

1311
00:57:28.185 --> 00:57:29.725
My work is underpinned

1312
00:57:29.825 --> 00:57:32.845
by the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child,

1313
00:57:33.095 --> 00:57:35.445
which enshrines Children's right to education,

1314
00:57:35.555 --> 00:57:37.605
privacy protection amongst others.

1315
00:57:38.625 --> 00:57:41.125
Now, there's an expectation under Article 12

1316
00:57:41.235 --> 00:57:44.205
that adults will meaningfully seek out, engage with,

1317
00:57:44.345 --> 00:57:45.845
and respond to the views

1318
00:57:46.185 --> 00:57:48.805
of children in all matter matters that concern them.

1319
00:57:49.625 --> 00:57:53.365
The U-N-C-R-C also reinforces a broader conceptualization

1320
00:57:53.745 --> 00:57:55.285
of children's experiences

1321
00:57:55.505 --> 00:57:57.605
and their knowledge about their experiences

1322
00:57:58.105 --> 00:57:59.525
as being unique and valuable.

1323
00:58:00.465 --> 00:58:03.125
In addition, general comment, 25 states

1324
00:58:03.315 --> 00:58:06.245
that national policy should be aimed at providing children

1325
00:58:06.635 --> 00:58:09.285
with the opportunity to benefit from engaging

1326
00:58:09.285 --> 00:58:10.445
with the digital environment

1327
00:58:10.585 --> 00:58:12.565
and ensuring their safe access to it.

1328
00:58:13.585 --> 00:58:16.805
Now, to address potential harms for young people online,

1329
00:58:17.125 --> 00:58:20.085
I think we need a collective response at tech

1330
00:58:20.345 --> 00:58:21.565
and education levels.

1331
00:58:22.425 --> 00:58:25.205
So rather than banning social media for under sixteens,

1332
00:58:25.365 --> 00:58:27.405
I advocate for rights-based response,

1333
00:58:27.705 --> 00:58:30.485
and I strongly support a digital duty of care approach.

1334
00:58:31.465 --> 00:58:34.205
So this approach would require tech companies

1335
00:58:34.205 --> 00:58:36.125
to regularly conduct risk assessments

1336
00:58:36.425 --> 00:58:38.845
to proactively identify harmful content.

1337
00:58:39.105 --> 00:58:41.045
And we can see that this has been brought in

1338
00:58:41.145 --> 00:58:42.365
in Australia at the moment.

1339
00:58:43.105 --> 00:58:44.765
Now, for example, in the eu,

1340
00:58:45.175 --> 00:58:48.565
users can submit online complaints about harmful material

1341
00:58:49.045 --> 00:58:50.125
directly to the tech companies

1342
00:58:50.545 --> 00:58:54.085
who are alleged legally obliged to act on these complaints.

1343
00:58:54.895 --> 00:58:57.925
Where a tech company refuses to remove this content,

1344
00:58:58.575 --> 00:59:01.725
users can complain to a digital services coordinator

1345
00:59:01.785 --> 00:59:02.845
to investigate further,

1346
00:59:03.395 --> 00:59:06.325
they can even pursue a court resolution if satisfactory

1347
00:59:06.605 --> 00:59:08.245
outcomes cannot be reached.

1348
00:59:08.905 --> 00:59:11.085
So regardless of age and maturity

1349
00:59:11.185 --> 00:59:12.845
and keeping in mind, these are different things,

1350
00:59:13.355 --> 00:59:14.525
this would place the onus

1351
00:59:14.525 --> 00:59:17.125
and tech companies to protect users of their platforms.

1352
00:59:17.825 --> 00:59:19.485
So other priority areas

1353
00:59:19.745 --> 00:59:23.045
of tech accountability include designing platforms

1354
00:59:23.315 --> 00:59:26.885
that prioritize safety, consent, and equity by default.

1355
00:59:27.345 --> 00:59:30.125
So, for example, having the highest privacy settings

1356
00:59:30.145 --> 00:59:33.485
as default, turning off geo tagging as default

1357
00:59:33.985 --> 00:59:36.485
and proactive rather than reactive moderation.

1358
00:59:37.325 --> 00:59:40.485
I think banning notify apps, so the apps used

1359
00:59:40.505 --> 00:59:44.045
to create DeepFakes or AI generated sexual abuse images,

1360
00:59:44.665 --> 00:59:47.125
but also the associated account accounts

1361
00:59:47.125 --> 00:59:51.005
and IP addresses by blocking related keywords

1362
00:59:51.005 --> 00:59:54.885
and using hashes for non AI generated sexual abuse images

1363
00:59:54.985 --> 00:59:56.365
so they can't be spread further.

1364
00:59:57.225 --> 01:00:01.405
And crews improving transparency in algorithmic decision

1365
01:00:01.405 --> 01:00:02.525
making, moderation

1366
01:00:02.625 --> 01:00:03.805
and content curation,

1367
01:00:04.685 --> 01:00:07.085
implementing stricter community guidelines,

1368
01:00:07.085 --> 01:00:11.085
including clear definitions of harmful content of material,

1369
01:00:11.705 --> 01:00:14.245
making it easier to report harmful content,

1370
01:00:14.355 --> 01:00:16.445
including defining reporting options,

1371
01:00:17.355 --> 01:00:20.685
providing age appropriate trauma, informed reporting

1372
01:00:20.745 --> 01:00:22.045
and redress mechanisms,

1373
01:00:22.465 --> 01:00:24.805
and partnering with researchers, educators,

1374
01:00:24.985 --> 01:00:28.085
and young people to co-create effective solutions.

1375
01:00:28.825 --> 01:00:31.565
And in addition, and just as importantly to this,

1376
01:00:31.925 --> 01:00:33.325
I think we need support

1377
01:00:33.505 --> 01:00:36.365
and resourcing for more robust education.

1378
01:00:36.985 --> 01:00:40.085
So we need youth focused programming aimed at building

1379
01:00:40.085 --> 01:00:42.885
digital resilience and promoting gender equality.

1380
01:00:43.625 --> 01:00:45.405
We need critical digital literacy,

1381
01:00:45.405 --> 01:00:47.645
including understanding algorithms.

1382
01:00:47.985 --> 01:00:49.645
So not just how to use the internet,

1383
01:00:49.645 --> 01:00:51.525
but how to behave ethically online,

1384
01:00:52.305 --> 01:00:54.405
how your data is being used or sold,

1385
01:00:54.785 --> 01:00:57.645
and again, algorithms, what you're being shown and why.

1386
01:00:58.225 --> 01:01:01.325
So, for example, digital literacy in Finland is,

1387
01:01:01.625 --> 01:01:05.005
it encompasses the technical skills to use digital tools,

1388
01:01:05.585 --> 01:01:07.805
the cognitive skills defined, evaluate

1389
01:01:07.805 --> 01:01:11.485
and create information, and the social skills to communicate

1390
01:01:11.585 --> 01:01:14.765
and collaborate online responsibly and ethically.

1391
01:01:15.025 --> 01:01:17.165
And this is embedded throughout the curriculum.

1392
01:01:17.625 --> 01:01:20.445
So the goal here is to empower individuals,

1393
01:01:20.495 --> 01:01:22.125
especially children and young people,

1394
01:01:22.625 --> 01:01:24.525
to navigate the digital world effectively,

1395
01:01:25.025 --> 01:01:26.965
to critically analyze online content

1396
01:01:27.225 --> 01:01:31.205
and participate in digital society safely and meaningfully.

1397
01:01:31.705 --> 01:01:34.205
And this is even more important now, we're seeing the rise

1398
01:01:34.225 --> 01:01:38.885
of ai, both in terms of AI generated sexual content,

1399
01:01:39.185 --> 01:01:42.125
but also AI companions, friends,

1400
01:01:42.515 --> 01:01:44.485
relationships, counselors, even.

1401
01:01:45.465 --> 01:01:48.845
We need better relationships and sexuality education.

1402
01:01:49.105 --> 01:01:51.565
So this goes beyond just critical literacy.

1403
01:01:52.185 --> 01:01:55.365
So this needs to be based upon a rights-based framework,

1404
01:01:55.375 --> 01:01:57.725
which covers digital ethical citizenship.

1405
01:01:58.265 --> 01:02:01.805
So unfortunately, our 2020 guidelines, which were inclusive

1406
01:02:01.905 --> 01:02:03.845
and holistic, have been formally removed.

1407
01:02:04.585 --> 01:02:08.005
And the draft framework lacks meaningful input from young

1408
01:02:08.005 --> 01:02:11.125
people, plus a disavow scope for conversations

1409
01:02:11.145 --> 01:02:13.365
around healthy digital relationships.

1410
01:02:13.825 --> 01:02:15.605
And again, the use of AI

1411
01:02:15.705 --> 01:02:18.485
or other forms of digital technology in those relationships.

1412
01:02:19.505 --> 01:02:23.245
We need mandatory consent education as early as possible.

1413
01:02:23.865 --> 01:02:26.525
We need investment in peer education initiatives.

1414
01:02:27.265 --> 01:02:30.045
We need to invest in public education campaigns

1415
01:02:30.045 --> 01:02:33.165
that promote digital citizenship, consent and respect.

1416
01:02:33.505 --> 01:02:36.685
And crucially, we must embed young people's voices,

1417
01:02:37.015 --> 01:02:40.485
their leadership and agency in all areas of policy

1418
01:02:40.625 --> 01:02:42.085
and educational initiatives.

1419
01:02:42.705 --> 01:02:44.285
So finally, it's my opinion

1420
01:02:44.395 --> 01:02:46.965
that young people don't need protection from access.

1421
01:02:47.435 --> 01:02:49.885
They need protection from abuse, neglect,

1422
01:02:50.115 --> 01:02:51.365
exclusion, and ignorance.

1423
01:02:51.715 --> 01:02:54.245
They don't not need us to unplug them, they need us

1424
01:02:54.245 --> 01:02:55.245
to plug in properly.

1425
01:02:55.895 --> 01:02:57.285
Young people are telling us

1426
01:02:57.285 --> 01:02:59.045
that they don't always feel safe online.

1427
01:02:59.585 --> 01:03:01.365
We need to hear them, and we need

1428
01:03:01.365 --> 01:03:03.365
to create safer digital spaces

1429
01:03:03.435 --> 01:03:05.805
that honor their voices, not punish them.

